org.gbif.common.parsers.date

Class CustomizedTextDateParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.common.parsers.date.CustomizedTextDateParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Parsable<TemporalAccessor>, TemporalParser

    public class CustomizedTextDateParser
extends Object
implements TemporalParser, Serializable
    Wrap a set of DateTimeFormatters to parse method.

    If the ISO format parsing process fails, use orderings formatters to parse the date.

        public ParseResult<TemporalAccessor> parse(String input,
                                           @Nullable
                                           DateComponentOrdering ordering)
        Description copied from interface: TemporalParser
        Parse a String date restricted to the ordering provided. Set a general date ordering for the parsing. For example, DMY will support both 14.08.2020 and 14/08/2020, but not 2020-08-14 or 08/14/2020. NOTE, this behaviour differs from TemporalParser.parse(String, DateComponentOrdering[]).
        Specified by:

      • parse

        public ParseResult<TemporalAccessor> parse(String input,
                                           @Nullable
                                           DateComponentOrdering[] orderings)
        Description copied from interface: TemporalParser
        Parse a String date to a TemporalAccessor, attempting unambiguous formats and the orderings provided. The date 2020-08-14 will always parse. An ordering of DMY_FORMATS will also support 14.08.2020, 14/08/2020 and 14/08/2020 14:11:00, but not 08/14/2020. NOTE, this behaviour differs from TemporalParser.parse(String, DateComponentOrdering).
        Specified by:
        parse in interface TemporalParser
